Russian President Vladimir Putin held a series of telephone conversations on Thursday and Friday with his counterparts from other countries of the Collective Security Treaty Organization (CSTO), including Kazakh President Kassym-Jomart Tokayev. The talks discussed the situation in Kazakhistan, Russian Presidential Press Secretary Dmitry Peskov told reporters on Friday, according to RIA News Agency. "They discussed the situation in Kazakhstan and joint actions within the CSTO to combat international terrorism and to ensure order as well as the security of the Kazakh citizens," Peskov said.